IPHONE PRIVACY SET UP
Safari + uBlock Origin Lite (or AdGuard adblocker if iOS 18.5 is not availablde) + Mullvad VPN + ATFP on "All Browsing.”


1. Go to Settings > Privacy & Security > Location Services > Instagram and select Never
2. Settings > Apps > Safari > Advanced > Advanced Tracking and Fingerprinting Protection
3. Crucial Step: Change the setting from "Private Browsing" to "All Browsing" to ensure protection remains active when you are not in an Incognito tab.
	1. Open the Settings app on your iPhone.
	2. Scroll down and tap Apps.
	3. Select Safari from the list of apps.
	4. Scroll to the very bottom and tap Advanced.
	5. Tap Advanced Tracking and Fingerprinting Protection.
	6. Select All Browsing (ensure a checkmark appears next to it).

	Note: If a website you trust stops working correctly, you can temporarily disable this for just that site by tapping the Page Settings (AA) icon in the Safari address bar and selecting "Reload Without Content Blockers" or a similar option for advanced privacy.

4. Install uBlock Origin Lite from the App Store.
5. Go to Settings > Safari > Extensions and enable it.
6. Crucial Step: In the extension settings within Safari, change the permission for All Websites to "Allow" instead of "Ask".
7. Install Mullvad VPN, use provided numerical code, CONNECT to GREECE server (make sure it is Green and says CONNECTED)

You will be using this stack to access Instagram:
Safari + uBlock Origin Lite + Mullvad VPN + ATFP on "All Browsing.”
YOU WILL NO LONGER USE THE INSTAGRAM APP